    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Zanthoxylum mildbraedii are inflammation, fever, and diarrhea, which can be effectively treated due to its anti-inflammatory, antipyretic, and antibacterial properties. Additionally, rheumatism, gastroenteritis, and malaria can also be alleviated as it possesses antimalarial, anti-inflammatory, and antimicrobial properties. Furthermore, the plant has been traditionally used to treat arthritis, fungal infections, and digestive issues, such as dyspepsia, by exhibiting antifungal, antibacterial, and carminative properties. Pain, skin irritation, and respiratory issues, including asthma, can be managed with its analgesic, anti-inflammatory, and expectorant properties. Insect bites, cough, diabetes, cholera, and gastrointestinal issues can also be treated with Zanthoxylum mildbraedii due to its analgesic, anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and antidiarrheal properties, as well as its ability to alleviate respiratory problems.",
